      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) is a superlative example of the analog era, powered by the legendary S54 3.2L inline-six featuring individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing. The high-revving powerplant delivers linear torque through a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual transmission to a factory-spec M-Variable Differential Lock. This specimen is mechanically flawless, having received proactive subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive cooling system overhaul. The chassis remains taut with no bushing deflection, and the factory paint retains a deep, swirl-free luster. Inside, the cabin is preserved in a time-capsule state, free from the typical wear on the Nappa leather bolsters. For the purist seeking a documented, mechanically sound icon, this E46 represents the zenith of naturally aspirated performance.",
